The valuation of the PIF-backed US electric vehicle company, Lucid, has increased to over $91 billion, surpassing Ford and General Motors. A recent stock market rally added over $17 billion to its valuation, up 24 percent, Bloomberg reported. The increase in shares comes after Lucid’s announcement to produce 20,000 vehicles in 2022. This happened amid a growing demand for EVs, as more consumers consider adopting the technology. Earlier, the stocks of the US automaker company, Rivian, jumped 15 percent, surpassing Volswagen’s market value, while Tesla gained 4.1 percent.